# UI Components Guide

## Overview

This project uses a comprehensive UI component library built on shadcn/ui and customized for the Neobrutalism design aesthetic. All components follow responsive design principles and work seamlessly with the unified typography system.

## Typography Components (`typography.tsx`)

**Priority: ALWAYS USE FIRST**

These components provide the foundation for all text in the application with comprehensive responsive scaling.

### Headings
- `H1` - Main page headings (text-xl → 2xl:text-6xl)
- `H2` - Section headings (text-lg → 2xl:text-4xl)  
- `H3` - Subsection headings (text-base → 2xl:text-3xl)
- `H4` - Small headings/labels (text-sm → 2xl:text-2xl)

### Body Text
- `Lead` - Important descriptive text with type variants (`foreground` | `default`)
- `L` - Large body text (text-sm → 2xl:text-2xl)
- `M` - Medium body text (text-xs → 2xl:text-lg)
- `S` - Small text (text-[0.625rem] → 2xl:text-base)
- `XS` - Extra small text (text-[0.5rem] → 2xl:text-sm)

### Specialized Text
- `Muted` - Muted/secondary text with mono font
- `SMuted` - Small muted text
- `Code` - Inline code snippets with background
- `Quote` - Regular quotes
- `LQuote` - Large quotes

**Usage Rules:**
- NEVER use raw HTML tags (`<p>`, `<h1>`, etc.) - always use typography components
- NEVER override responsive sizing with custom classes
- Use `className` prop for styling but preserve responsive behavior
- Automatic title-case formatting applied to headings

## Layout Components

### Section (`section.tsx`)
Comprehensive layout wrapper with background and column support.

**Props:**
- `background`: `'grid'` | `'mask'` | `'none'`
- `columns`: `1` | `2` (enables Section.Left/Section.Right/Section.Bottom)
- `fullHeight`: boolean (min-h-[100svh])
- `centerContent`: boolean
- `maxWidth`, `padding`, `containerClassName`
- `as`: ElementType (render as different element)

**Two-Column Usage:**
```tsx
<Section columns={2}>
  <Section.Left>Left content</Section.Left>
  <Section.Right>Right content</Section.Right>
  <Section.Bottom>Full-width bottom content</Section.Bottom>
</Section>
```

### Background Grid (`background-grid.tsx`)
Grid background for hero-style sections - used internally by Section component.

## Interactive Components

### Button (`button.tsx`)
Core interactive element with Neobrutalism styling.

**Variants:**
- `default` - Main buttons with shadow effects
- `neutral` - Neutral styling without shadows
- `noShadow` - Flat button style
- `accent` - Accent-colored button
- `link` - Text link styling
- `action` - Full-width action button with enhanced hover

**Sizes:** `default`, `sm`, `lg`, `icon`

### NeoBadge (`neoBadge.tsx`)
Stylized badges for categories, labels, and interactive elements.

**Variants:** `default`, `dark`, `light`, `outline`
**Rotation:** `none`, `slight`, `negative`, `medium`, `negativeMedium`
**Interactive:** `none`, `grow`, `lift`, `bounce`, `wiggle`
**Size:** `sm`, `md`, `lg` (no text sizing - use with typography components)

### IconLink (`icon-link.tsx`)
Link components with icon support and Neobrutalism styling.

**Components:**
- `IconLink` - Full button-style link with icon
- `CornerIconLink` - Minimal icon-only link for corners

**Props:**
- `iconPosition`: `'left'` | `'right'`
- `external`: boolean (adds target="_blank")
- Inherits all Button variants and sizes

## Content Components

### Card (`card.tsx`)
Primary content containers with comprehensive variant system.

**Variants:**
- `default` - Standard card styling
- `reversed` - Light background
- `outline` - Transparent background  
- `accent` - Accent-colored card
- `clickable` - Interactive hover states

**Features:**
- `rotation`: `slight`, `slightNegative`, `medium`, `mediumNegative`
- `interactive`: `slight`, `medium` (hover effects)
- `shadow`: `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`
- `borderStyle`: `default`, `accent`, `none`
- `disableScale`: boolean (disable responsive scaling)

**Structure:** `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardContent`, `CardFooter`, `CardTitle`, `CardDescription`

