## Component Usage Hierarchy

### 1. Typography First
Always start with typography components for any text content.

### 2. Layout Structure  
Use Section for page layout, Card for content containers.

### 3. Interactive Elements
Button for actions, IconLink for navigation, NeoBadge for labels.

### 4. Specialized Components
Use specific components (ProfileImage, Carousel, etc.) for specialized needs.

## Best Practices

### Do's
- ✅ Use typography components exclusively for text
- ✅ Leverage component variants instead of custom styling
- ✅ Follow the Neobrutalism aesthetic with borders, shadows, rotations
- ✅ Use Section for consistent layouts
- ✅ Compose Card with CardHeader/CardContent/CardFooter
- ✅ Apply interactive props (rotation, hover effects) for playfulness

### Don'ts  
- ❌ Never use raw HTML text elements (`<p>`, `<h1>`, etc.)
- ❌ Don't override responsive typography sizing
- ❌ Avoid custom shadows/borders - use component variants
- ❌ Don't mix Badge and NeoBadge - prefer NeoBadge for this design
- ❌ Don't create custom layout grids - use Section columns

### Custom Styling
When custom styling is needed:
- Use `className` prop to extend, not override
- Preserve component responsive behavior
- Follow Neobrutalism principles (thick borders, bold colors, rotations)
- Use CSS variables for theming consistency

### Responsive Behavior
- All components support responsive scaling
- Typography scales automatically across 5 breakpoints
- Cards have optional responsive scaling (`disableScale` to opt-out)
- Sections adapt layout for mobile/desktop
- Interactive elements maintain touch-friendly sizing

### Accessibility
- All components include proper ARIA attributes
- Focus states are clearly visible
- Color contrast meets accessibility standards
- Keyboard navigation is fully supported
- Screen reader compatibility maintained

